s code block with no language specified');\n  it('adds highlighted class to processed blocks');\n  it('preserves code block content');\n  it('handles empty code blocks');\n  it('does not modify inline code');\n});\n```\nImport: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n```ts\ndescribe('taxonomy plugin', () => {\n  it('builds tag index from file tags');\n  it('generates tag listing pages in ctx.output');\n  it('handles files with no tags');\n  it('handles files with multiple tags');\n  it('tag pages list all files with that tag');\n  it('stores tag map in ctx.data');\n  it('handles empty file list');\n  it('tags are case-normalized to lowercase');\n});\n```\nImport: `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n```ts\ndescribe('rss-feed plugin', () => {\n  it('generates valid RSS 2.0 XML');\n  it('feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown');\n  it('feed items include category tags from taxonomy');\n  it('feed includes channel title from config');\n  it('feed items sorted by date newest first');\n  it('handles files without dates');\n  it('feed link uses baseUrl from config');\n});\n```\nImport: `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n```ts\ndescribe('search-index plugin', () => {\n  it('generates search-index.json in ctx.output');\n  it('index entries have title, slug, and plain text content');\n  it('HTML tags stripped from indexed content');\n  it('code blocks included in searchable text');\n  it('handles empty file list');\n  it('search index is valid JSON');\n  it('index entries include tags if present');\n});\n```\nImport: `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n```ts\ndescribe('sitemap plugin', () => {\n  it('generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output');\n  it('includes all content page URLs');\n  it('includes taxonomy tag page URLs');\n  it('includes feed.xml URL');\n  it('URLs use baseUrl from config');\n  it('sitemap is valid XML structure');\n  it('handles site with no tag pages');\n});\n```\nImport: `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n```ts\ndescribe('dev-server plugin', () => {\n  it('stores dev-server-config in ctx.data');\n  it('config includes port setting');\n  it('config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline');\n  it('config includes search index path');\n  it('config includes content routes');\n  it('default port is 3000');\n  it('handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully');\n});\n```\nImport: `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Interface Contract (Full Detail)\n\nThe `Plugin` interface is defined in `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`:\n\n```ts\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;              // unique identifier (e.g., \"markdown-ext\")\n  version: string;           // semver string (e.g., \"1.0.0\")\n  dependencies: string[];    // names of plugins this depends on (used for topological sort)\n  hooks: PluginHooks;        // lifecycle hooks\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Lifecycle execution order** (from `BuildEngine.build()`):\n1. `beforeBuild` -- called once per plugin, in topological dependency order\n2. `transformContent` -- called for each file, in topological plugin order (plugins applied one after another across all files)\n3. Template rendering happens (not a plugin hook)\n4. `afterBuild` -- called once per plugin, in topological dependency order\n\n**BuildContext** is the shared state passed through all hooks:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- site configuration (title, baseUrl, outputDir, contentDir, templateDir)\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- the mutable array of content files (transformed in place during transformContent phase)\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path to rendered content (plugins can add entries like `feed.xml`, `sitemap.xml`, `search-index.json`, `tags/xxx.html`)\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path to binary data\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store for cross-plugin communication (e.g., `taxonomy-tags`, `asset-manifest`, `dev-server-config`)\n\n**Each plugin must export** a factory function named `createXxxPlugin()` that returns a `Plugin` object.\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Dependency DAG\n\n```\nWave 1 (no deps):     markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight, taxonomy\nWave 2 (Wave 1 deps): rss-feed       (depends: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n                       search-index   (depends: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\nWave 3 (Wave 2 deps): sitemap        (depends: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n                       dev-server     (depends: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n```\n\n## Cross-Plugin Data Contracts (from test assertions)\n\n| Data Key | Set By | Read By | Type |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `taxonomy-tags` | taxonomy (beforeBuild) | rss-feed, sitemap | `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` |\n| `asset-manifest` | asset-pipeline (transformContent) | dev-server | `{ assets: string[] }` |\n| `dev-server-config` | dev-server (afterBuild) | -- | `{ port: number, routes: Array<{path, handler}>, assetPaths: string[], searchIndexPath: string }` |\n\nOutput entries added by plugins:\n- `feed.xml` -- by rss-feed (afterBuild)\n- `sitemap.xml` -- by sitemap (afterBuild)\n- `search-index.json` -- by search-index (afterBuild)\n- `tags/{tagname}.html` -- by taxonomy (afterBuild)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Test Counts\n\n| Test file | Count |\n|---|---|\n| core.test.ts | 15 |\n| markdown-ext.test.ts | 8 |\n| asset-pipeline.